&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;5+ years of enterprise sales experience in life sciences, with demonstrated success covering pharmaceutical companies, biotechnology firms, and/or research organizations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A track record of managing complex sales cycles within life sciences organizations and securing strategic deals by understanding both technical requirements and scientific/regulatory use cases&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Extensive experience negotiating complex agreements within life sciences procurement frameworks, including understanding of R&amp;amp;D budget cycles and compliance requirements&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Proven experience exceeding revenue targets in the life sciences sector by effectively managing an evolving pipeline and sales process&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent communication skills and the ability to present confidently to various life sciences audiences, from researchers and scientists to R&amp;amp;D leadership and C-suite executives&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deep understanding of life sciences buying cycles, decision-making processes, and key pain points across pharmaceutical, biotech, and research organizations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A strategic, analytical approach to assessing the life sciences market combined with creative, tactical execution to capture opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A passion for and/or experience with advanced AI systems and their applications in life sciences. You feel strongly about ensuring frontier AI systems are developed safely and ethically for scientific and clinical applications&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to develop and refine life sciences use cases for AI in collaboration with customers and channel partners, with particular focus on drug discovery, clinical development, regulatory submissions, and commercial operations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
